Package: pcdp-lint
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: command-line tool for validating PCDP specification files
 pcdp-lint is a command-line tool for validating Post-Coding Development
 Paradigm (PCDP) specification files. It validates PCDP specification files
 against 13 structural rules including required sections, META fields,
 deployment template resolution, and cross-section consistency.
 .
 The tool supports strict mode (treating warnings as errors), template
 listing, and provides detailed diagnostic output with line numbers and
 error categories. It recognizes various deployment templates including
 cli-tool, backend-service, verified-library, and others.
 .
 pcdp-lint is a static binary with no runtime dependencies, does not make
 network calls or modify input files, and follows clean exit patterns
 for SIGTERM and SIGINT signals.